<DOC><DOCNO> AP890522-0124 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-22-89 1601EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-TransplantBaby     05-22 0206</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Transplant Baby,0212</SECOND><HEAD>Youngest Multitransplant Baby Has Third Birthday</HEAD><DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The youngest person ever to undergo four livertransplants has celebrated her third birthday playing with a newBarbie doll and swing set.   ``There was a time when I didn't think we'd see her firstbirthday, let alone her third,'' said Shirley LaRocco said of herdaughter, Meghann.   ``But our prayers were answered, and now she's doing justfine,'' she said. ``We're just so excited she's doing so well. Thisis the first year she's known it's her birthday.''   She said Meghann played with her gifts for most of the daySunday.   Meghann was born with biliary atresia, a a fatal liver defect,and complications necessitated the series of transplants inNovember and December 1986.   Chicagoans rushed donations to the family to help defray medicalcosts. Officials of the University of Chicago Hospitals hadestimated the cost of Meghann's treatment at $500,000.   Doctors estimate Meghann's chances for a full recovery at 80percent to 85 percent. She no longer has to make regular visits tothe doctor but continues to take an anti-rejection drug,cyclosporine, every day.   ``She's just like any normal child now,'' said her father,Frank. ``She's even taking roller-skating lessons.''</TEXT></DOC>